const MANIFESTO=[{"id":"t1-001","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Proportional Representation","desc":"TVK’s policy is that true social justice lies in every community receiving proportional representation in due measure. To ensure this, a Caste Survey (Caste-wise calculation study) will be undertaken.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Proportional Representation","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-002","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Claiming Financial Distribution for Tamil Nadu","desc":"A resolution will be passed in the Tamil Nadu Legislative Assembly to claim the fair and complete financial share due to Tamil Nadu from the taxes paid by Tamil Nadu to the Union government. Instead of stopping with passing a resolution, a special legal com…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Claiming Financial Distribution","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-003","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Protection of Tamil Nadu's rights in Constituency Delimitation","desc":"TVK severely opposes the delimitation of Parliamentary constituencies on the basis of population. Actions will be taken to bring appropriate legal amendments to prevent the Southern states from being severely affected by constituency delimitation.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Protection of Tamil","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-004","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Opposition to One Nation One Election","desc":"TVK severely opposes the Union government's 'One Nation, One Election' plan which weakens state autonomy and the principle of federalism. Therefore, appropriate efforts will be taken to withdraw the 'One Nation, One Election' draft bill.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Opposition to One","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-005","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Protection of Two-Language Policy","desc":"The Three-Language Education Plan that the Union government attempts to impose through the New Education Policy will severely affect Tamil Nadu's linguistic heritage and the quality of education. On behalf of TVK, a resolution will be passed in the Legislat…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Protection of Two-Language","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-006","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Abolition of NEET Exam","desc":"Pressure will be continuously given to the Union government on behalf of TVK to abolish the NEET exam.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Abolition of NEET","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-007","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"State Language in High Courts","desc":"It will be insisted to use the respective state languages as the court language in High Courts.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"State Language in","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-008","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Supreme Court Branch in Chennai","desc":"It will be continuously insisted to the Union government on behalf of TVK for a branch of the Supreme Court to be located in Chennai. Aram (virtue) Thoon 01","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Supreme Court Branch","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-009","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Cauvery River Water Rights","desc":"TVK will obtain the share due to Tamil Nadu in the Cauvery water as per the 2018 Supreme Court judgment. Immediate legal actions will be taken against the barriers created in obtaining the water due to Tamil Nadu. Actions will be taken to further strengthen…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Cauvery River Water","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t1-010","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Katchatheevu Fishing Rights","desc":"Sincere and emotional pressure will be given to the Union government on behalf of TVK to take appropriate actions to reclaim and maintain the traditional fishing rights of Indian-Tamil fishermen in the Gulf of Mannar as per the Katchatheevu agreement made b…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Katchatheevu Fishing Rights","personas":["fisher","all"]},{"id":"t1-011","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Justice for Sri Lankan Tamils","desc":"It will be insisted to the Union government on behalf of TVK to provide Indian citizenship to the Sri Lankan Tamils living in Tamil Nadu, having migrated from Sri Lanka. Through this action, it will be ensured that Sri Lankan Tamils receive all the welfare …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Justice for Sri","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-012","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Identity and Pride","desc":"B. Tamil Language, Culture and Heritage","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Identity and","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-013","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Budget for Tamil Heritage and Civilization","desc":"To proclaim and protect the history of Tamils, who possess a unique heritage and pride in world history, Tamil cultural sites will be restructured at an expense of 500 crore rupees. Traditional Tamil cultural arts including Silambam, Kummiyaattam, Kolaattam…","metric":"500 crore","scheme":"","short":"Budget for Tamil","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-014","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Archaeological Excavation","desc":"TVK will support the Department of Archaeology to continue archaeological excavations at 10 sites: Keeladi, Adichanallur, Kodumanal, Mayiladumpaarai, Sivakalai, Azhagankulam, Arikamedu, Saluvankuppam, Kaveripattinam, and Poompuhar. Efforts will be taken to …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Archaeological Excavation","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-015","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"'Tamil Civilization Museum' in Madurai","desc":"To proclaim thousands of years of Tamil history, a 'Tamil Civilization Museum' of international standards will be established in Madurai.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"'Tamil Civilization Museum'","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t1-016","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Folk Artists Welfare Improvement","desc":"Two schemes will be implemented to encourage folk arts and artists who serve as the cultural roots of Tamils. Scheme to protect the livelihood of folk artists: Opportunities to express their artistic talent in government functions and programs will be creat…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Folk Artists Welfare","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-017","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Victorious Tamil Nadu","desc":"* Young Artist Incentive Scheme: To encourage growing young folk artists, an allowance of 25 thousand rupees per year will be given to one thousand young artists.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Victorious Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-018","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Folk Art Research and Training Centers","desc":"Folk Art Research and Training Centers will be established in Coimbatore (Karagaattam, Kummi, Oyilaattam), Thanjavur (Bharatanatyam, Therukoothu, Parai), and Tirunelveli (Silambam, Kambaattam), and free training will be given to interested students.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Folk Art Research","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t1-019","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Traditional Sports Development Scheme","desc":"The following schemes will be implemented to reclaim, encourage, and grow the traditional sports of Tamil Nadu. To bring traditional Tamil sports to the world level, the Tamil Nadu Rural Olympic Series will be conducted. A financial aid of 5 lakh rupees wil…","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Traditional Sports Development","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-020","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Thirukkural Development Scheme","desc":"A special scheme will be introduced with the aim of making the Thirukkural a functional part of every student's life. Cash prizes and educational scholarships will be provided to students who have fully learned and mastered 300 Kurals; Global cultural exper…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Thirukkural Development Scheme","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t1-021","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Pension for Language War Martyrs","desc":"To honor the sacrifice of the Language War martyrs, the pension provided to their families will be increased to two and a half lakh (₹2,50,000) each per year. To remember the Language War martyrs, speech competitions and essay competitions will be conducted…","metric":"₹2,50,000","scheme":"","short":"Pension for Language","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-022","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Artificial Intelligence","desc":"After the arrival of the technology called Artificial Intelligence (AI), all sectors have adapted themselves accordingly. However, Artificial Intelligence technology is based on English. Designing and using this technology in the Tamil language becomes a ne…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Artificial Intelligence","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-023","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Cultural Digital Archives","desc":"Necessary funds will be allocated to create digital archives to protect the art, culture, and heritage of Tamil Nadu.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Cultural Digital","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-024","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Nadu Digital Museum","desc":"Under the Tamil Nadu Digital Museum scheme, efforts will be taken to document Tamil history, heritage, and culture through AR (Augmented Reality), VR (Virtual Reality), and Hologram. Aram (virtue) Thoon 01","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Digital","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-025","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Nadu Responsible Tourism","desc":"Instead of considering tourism only as an entertainment feature, TVK’s ‘Tamil Nadu Responsible Tourism’ puts forward a happy and creative tourism plan encompassing eco-tourism, heritage tourism, coastal tourism, and cultural tourism. 25 percent of the reven…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Responsible","personas":["fisher","all"]},{"id":"t1-026","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Archaeological Excavation (Context: Archaeological Tourism)","desc":"The following initiatives will be implemented with the aim of attracting tourists by centering on Tamil culture. Folk art programs will be conducted every evening at 10 important tourist sites. Rural tourism centers providing rural life experiences will be …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Archaeological Excavation (Context:","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-027","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Spiritual Tourism Scheme","desc":"A Tamil Nadu Spiritual Tourism Scheme will be created on four important spiritual routes. The Arupadai Veedu Tourism Scheme encompassing the spiritual sites of Palani, Thirupparankunram, Thiruchendur, Swami Malai, Thiruthani, and Pazhamudircholai. The Saiva…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Spiritual Tourism Scheme","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-028","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Pilgrim Rest Houses","desc":"Rest houses for pilgrims will be established in Thiruvannamalai, Madurai, Rameswaram, Palani, Velankanni, and Nagore, which serve as important spiritual places of worship for all religions.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Pilgrim Rest Houses","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-029","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Cultural Tourism Scheme","desc":"The Tamil urban civilization experience will be reconstructed for tourists through AR (Augmented Reality) and VR (Virtual Reality) at heritage sites including Keeladi, Adichanallur, Kodumanal, and Gangai Konda Cholapuram.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Cultural Tourism","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-030","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Cultural Lodges","desc":"Tax concessions will be provided to private owners who convert Chettinad houses, Nilgiris bungalows, etc., which reflect Tamil heritage and culture, into lodging houses. Furthermore, 50 percent of the expense incurred for restructuring those traditional bui…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Cultural Lodges","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-031","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Nadu Maritime Route Tourism","desc":"A maritime tourism route will be established starting from Vedaranyam along the long coastline of Tamil Nadu up to Rameswaram Mandapam. The respective local fishermen themselves will function as guides for tourists in the respective areas and as sailors who…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Maritime","personas":["fisher","all"]},{"id":"t1-032","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Nilgiris Mountain Adventure Tourism","desc":"15 trekking routes will be identified in Ooty, Coonoor, Gudalur, Kotagiri, and Mudumalai, and a Nilgiris Mountain Adventure Tourism Scheme will be implemented. A Nilgiris Mountain Biking Festival will be conducted every year without affecting the ecology. P…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Nilgiris Mountain Adventure","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-033","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Caravan Tourism","desc":"The first Caravan Tourism policy will be created in Tamil Nadu. Under it: * Beautiful landscapes will be selected in 20 tourism zones throughout Tamil Nadu, and caravan stops with drinking water, internet facility, electricity connection, and toilet facilit…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Caravan Tourism","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t1-034","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Food Tourism Route","desc":"To taste the traditional food varieties in Tamil Nadu, a Chettinad Food Tourism Route (Karaikudi, Kanadukathan, Devakottai), a Kongu Food Tourism Route (Coimbatore, Erode, Salem), and a Tirunelveli Food Tourism Route will be created. An international food f…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Food Tourism Route","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t1-035","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"River-based Tourism","desc":"River-based tourism will be created on three important river routes: the Cauvery river route from Hogenakkal Falls to Srirangam Island, the Madurai Vaigai route, and the Thamirabarani river route from Papanasam to Tirunelveli.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"River-based Tourism","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t1-036","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tourism Skill Development Scheme","desc":"12-week training classes encompassing hospitality, food preparation, tour guide, water sports safety management, and artistic skill development will be introduced. Employment will be ensured for those who pass them.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tourism Skill Development","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-037","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Cinema Tourism","desc":"A Cinema Tourism Route encompassing famous filming sites throughout Tamil Nadu will be created. Arrangements will be made to know the details regarding the connection between those places and films through QR codes.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Cinema Tourism","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t1-038","thoon":1,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tourism Safety","desc":"To improve safety features for tourists, infrastructure facilities and basic facilities at tourist sites will be improved. Specifically, facilities including qualified operators, coastal life savers, tourist police, and 24-hour functioning help centers will…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tourism Safety","personas":["fisher","all"]},{"id":"t2-039","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Poverty-free Tamil Nadu","desc":"TVK’s primary objective is that a poverty-free Tamil Nadu must be created. Poor families in Tamil Nadu will be identified, and it will be ensured that all government welfare schemes reach them. Furthermore, appropriate employment opportunities will be creat…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Poverty-free Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-040","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Free Electricity","desc":"200 units of free electricity per month will be provided to eligible households.","metric":"200 units","scheme":"","short":"Free Electricity","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-041","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Drinking Water for All","desc":"100 percent clean drinking water supply will be ensured to all households in Tamil Nadu.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Drinking Water for","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-042","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Housing for All","desc":"5 lakh new houses will be built and given so that the poor and simple people in rural areas can get their own house.","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Housing for All","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-043","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Regularization of Patta","desc":"Government Patta will be provided to everyone living on government poramboke lands (provided there is no objection). The M.G.R. Patta documents currently held by people living in hilly areas including Kalrayan will be formally computerized. Aram (virtue) Th…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Regularization of Patta","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-044","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Doorstep Ration Products","desc":"Priority will be given to the elderly, differently-abled, and marginalized people, and ration products will be distributed by going to their houses.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Doorstep Ration Products","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-045","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Nutritious Food Products","desc":"To avoid the public being affected by anemia, and Vitamin A and B-12 deficiencies, iron and folic acid-enriched rice, Vitamin A and Vitamin D-enriched cooking oil, and fortified wheat flour will be distributed to everyone through ration shops. Through this,…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Nutritious Food Products","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-046","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Ration Products Packed in Packets","desc":"To prevent underweight, poor quality, adulteration, and smuggling in ration products, and to ensure that quality products at fair weights reach the public, all ration products except rice will be distributed as packets.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Ration Products Packed","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-047","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Full Stop to Adulteration","desc":"At every stage of the public distribution system, severe quality checks will be performed. Through this, it will be ensured that unadulterated quality products are distributed to the people.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Full Stop to","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-048","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Increase in Ration Shops","desc":"One ration shop will be established for every 500 ration cards. Through this, overcrowding will be avoided, and service quality will be ensured. Through this, everyone can easily obtain ration products.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Increase in Ration","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-049","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Appointment of Weighers","desc":"Sufficient weighers will be appointed in every rural ration shop. Female employees for women and male employees for men will be appointed. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Appointment of Weighers","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t2-050","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Dignified Life and Social Security","desc":"B. Adi Dravidar and Tribal Welfare","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Dignified Life and","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-051","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Social Justice Budget","desc":"The funds allocated in the budget for the welfare of Adi Dravidar-Tribal and marginalized community people will be fully used for their development. These funds will never be used for other development schemes.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Social Justice Budget","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-052","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Adi Dravidar Assistance","desc":"An assistance of 40 thousand rupees per year will be provided to Adi Dravidar - Tribal students studying professional education, medicine, law, and administration. Through this, the higher education of Adi Dravidar-Tribal students being blocked due to pover…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Adi Dravidar Assistance","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t2-053","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Adi Dravidar Entrepreneur Scheme","desc":"Through the Scheduled Caste Entrepreneur Scheme, 5 lakh rupees will be provided as investment amount to first-generation entrepreneurs belonging to Adi Dravidar - Tribal communities.","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Adi Dravidar Entrepreneur","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t2-054","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"TAHDCO Loan Waiver","desc":"Loans taken by Adi Dravidar people from the Tamil Nadu Adi Dravidar Housing and Development Corporation will be completely waived.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"TAHDCO Loan Waiver","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-055","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Adi Dravidar and Tribal Housing Scheme","desc":"Permanent housing and Patta will be provided to all Adi Dravidar and Tribal people in Tamil Nadu.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Adi Dravidar and","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-056","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Prevention of SC/ST Atrocities","desc":"Atrocities against Adi Dravidar and Tribal people will be completely prevented. A separate police wing will be established for this under the leadership of the respective District Superintendent of Police. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Prevention of SC/ST","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-057","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Minority Education and Entrepreneur Contribution","desc":"Schemes for minority education will be implemented within the planned time. Skill development centers will be established in every district. Colleges for minority women will be opened through the Waqf Board. The method of obtaining necessary financial aid f…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Minority Education and","personas":["business","youth","woman","all"]},{"id":"t2-058","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Legal struggle against the Waqf Amendment Act","desc":"TVK government will conduct a legal struggle in the Supreme Court to permanently remove the new Waqf Amendment Act. Holy Pilgrimage Assistance for people of all religions The Haj subsidy for Muslims undertaking the Haj pilgrimage will be increased. The subs…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Legal struggle against","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-059","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Place for Burial Grounds and Kabristans","desc":"Sufficient places for burial grounds (Kabristans) and interment sites for minorities will be selected and allocated. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Place for Burial","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-060","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Old Age Assistance","desc":"Old age assistance will be increased to three thousand (₹3,000) rupees.","metric":"₹3,000","scheme":"","short":"Old Age Assistance","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-061","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Free Holy Pilgrimage","desc":"Arrangements will be made to take two and a half lakh senior citizens every year on holy pilgrimage to places they desire. In this, facilities including AC train facility, comfortable lodging, and good food will be provided.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Free Holy Pilgrimage","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-062","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Vettri Mobile Senior Clinic","desc":"1000 mobile senior clinics will be started throughout Tamil Nadu for senior citizens. In every mobile clinic, there will be one doctor, one nurse, and one physiotherapist. They will personally go to every Gram Panchayat throughout Tamil Nadu and perform fre…","metric":"","scheme":"Vettri Mobile Senior Clinic","short":"Vettri Mobile Senior","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-063","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Senior Equipment Assistance","desc":"A financial aid of ten thousand rupees will be provided for senior citizens to buy essential equipment including walking sticks, spectacles, wheelchairs, hearing aids, and sets of teeth.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Senior Equipment Assistance","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-064","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Old Age Home","desc":"Old age homes equipped with all features necessary for seniors including qualified caretakers, medical staff, and entertainment facilities will be established in every district.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Old Age Home","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-065","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Senior Recreation Clubs","desc":"Senior recreation clubs with facilities including a library, yoga and meditation classes, and indoor games will be established. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Senior Recreation Clubs","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-066","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Senior Citizens in Governance Administration","desc":"To utilize the experience and talents of senior citizens, their advice will also be obtained in the governance administration.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Senior Citizens in","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-067","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Senior Citizen Protection Wing","desc":"A Senior Citizen Protection Wing will be created in every District Superintendent of Police office. A separate Nodal Officer will be appointed in it, and problems such as property issues, harassment, and abandonment against the elderly will be solved.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Senior Citizen Protection","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-068","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Doorstep Government Services","desc":"Important government services including ration card renewal and provision of certificates will be provided by going to the houses of senior citizens.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Doorstep Government Services","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-069","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Pension Hike","desc":"The monthly pension for the differently-abled will be increased to three thousand (₹3,000) rupees.","metric":"₹3,000","scheme":"","short":"Pension Hike","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-070","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Education for Special Children","desc":"An exclusive teacher for special children will be appointed in every government school. Similarly, exclusive schools for special children will also be opened.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Education for Special","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-071","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Equipment Assistance","desc":"Assistance will be provided for the differently-abled to buy essential wheelchairs, spectacles, hearing aids, and walking equipment. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Equipment Assistance","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-072","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Transgender Welfare and Dignity Protection Act","desc":"The following schemes will be introduced with the aim of protecting transgender welfare. * A consolidated pay of 3,000 rupees will be provided. * Skill development training will be provided so that transgenders can obtain employment. * Help will be given to…","metric":"3,000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Transgender Welfare and","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-073","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Weaver Assistance","desc":"Tamil Nadu's weavers are the most talented artists in the world. Yet their livelihood is still in a severe struggle. To remove that, an assistance of 30 thousand rupees per year will be provided to every weaver family that owns a loom (powerloom/handloom). …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Weaver Assistance","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-074","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Weaver Raw Material Procurement Subsidy","desc":"A 50 percent subsidy will be provided to weavers for buying raw materials including yarn, dye, and chemicals required for the weaving industry.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Weaver Raw Material","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-075","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Free Electricity for Powerlooms","desc":"The free electricity currently provided to houses where handlooms are installed will be increased to 500 units. Similarly, the free electricity for houses where powerlooms are installed will be increased to 1500 units. A 75 percent subsidy will be provided …","metric":"500 units","scheme":"","short":"Free Electricity for","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-076","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Life Insurance","desc":"Life insurance worth 10 lakh rupees will be provided to all weavers.","metric":"10 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Life Insurance","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-077","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Savings and Protection Scheme","desc":"The government contribution amount in the Tamil Nadu Cooperative Handloom Weaver Savings and Protection Scheme is currently 8 percent. This amount will be increased to 16 percent.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Savings and Protection","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-078","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Integrated Weaver Towns","desc":"Integrated weaver towns will be created in Kanchipuram, Arani, Salem, and Erode districts which excel in the weaving industry. Solar panels with 3 kilowatt capacity will be installed for the electricity requirement of these towns.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Integrated Weaver Towns","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-079","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Weaver Children Assistance","desc":"Assistance will be provided for weaver children to study higher education in Design and Textile Engineering.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Weaver Children Assistance","personas":["weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-080","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Vettri Thari (Victorious Loom)","desc":"An exclusive e-commerce brand will be created to directly sell the products of Tamil Nadu weavers at the international level. Vettri Thari showrooms will be established in every important city. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"Vettri Thari (Victorious Loom)","short":"Vettri Thari (Victorious","personas":["youth","weaver","all"]},{"id":"t2-081","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Solar Panel Subsidy","desc":"A 100 percent subsidy will be provided to install solar panels for individual-owned loom sheds.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Solar Panel Subsidy","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-082","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Implementing the Old Pension Scheme","desc":"The Tamil Nadu Guaranteed Pension Scheme brought by the DMK government will be abolished, and as per the request of government employees, a complete Old Pension Scheme will be kindly considered and evaluated.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Implementing the Old","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-083","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Government Employee Welfare Board","desc":"A Government Employee Welfare Board will be established with an allocation of ₹5,000 crore to protect the rights and ensure the welfare of government employees including government staff, police personnel, school teachers, and college professors.","metric":"₹5,000 crore","scheme":"","short":"Government Employee Welfare","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t2-084","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Regularization of Temporary Staff","desc":"Temporary staff appointed on a contract basis in government jobs including teachers and nurses will be appointed as permanent staff after completing 5 years of service experience.","metric":"5 years","scheme":"","short":"Regularization of Temporary","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-085","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Transparency in Promotion and Workplace Transfer","desc":"It will be ensured that promotions and workplace transfers of government employees take place honestly and with transparency.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Transparency in Promotion","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-086","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Immediate Implementation of the 8th Pay Commission","desc":"As soon as the Union government announces it, the TVK government will immediately implement the 8th Pay Commission in the state for the benefit of government employees. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Immediate Implementation of","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-087","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Police Welfare Scheme","desc":"A Police Welfare and Work Reform Act will be brought and weekly off will be given on a rotation basis. The police laundry allowance will be increased from 500 rupees to 1000 rupees. Police welfare hospitals will be established in districts including Madurai…","metric":"500 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Police Welfare Scheme","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-088","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Police Honorarium","desc":"To honor police officers who act bravely in the duty of protecting law and order and lose their lives, 1 crore rupees will be provided to their families as honorarium.","metric":"1 crore","scheme":"","short":"Police Honorarium","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-089","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Dignified Salary and Welfare for Police","desc":"The basic monthly salary of police officers will be increased from the current ₹18,200 to ₹25,000. Furthermore, an additional monthly incentive (Duty Allowance) of ₹1,000 will be provided to police officers working in divisions with high workload.","metric":"₹18,200","scheme":"","short":"Dignified Salary and","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-090","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Transparent and Accountable Police Administration","desc":"A transparent and accountable police administration without political interference in police transfers and appointments will be ensured. All decisions will be taken only on the basis of administrative requirements, performance metrics, and professional inte…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Transparent and Accountable","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-091","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Abolition of Orderly System","desc":"The system of appointing police officers as orderlies in the houses of VIPs against the rules in Tamil Nadu will be stopped. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Abolition of Orderly","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-092","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Sufficient Police Quarters in all districts","desc":"To facilitate the stay of families of police officers who go on transfer and special duties, it will be ensured that there are sufficient police quarters in all districts.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Sufficient Police Quarters","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-093","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Women Police Welfare","desc":"The involvement of women police officers in bandobast duties will be stopped. It will be ensured that they are appointed as front-line police officers.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Women Police Welfare","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t2-094","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Equal Work! Equal Pay!","desc":"A Tamil Nadu Teacher Protection Act will be brought, and those among the teachers working temporarily who have completed 5 years will be converted into permanent teachers. Similarly, it will be ensured that during the period they work as temporary teachers,…","metric":"5 years","scheme":"","short":"Equal Work! Equal","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-095","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Foreign training for Government School Teachers","desc":"To improve the qualification of government school teachers, qualified teachers selected every year will be taken to receive training in Singapore and Finland, which excel in school education.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Foreign training for","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-096","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Teacher Appointment","desc":"All vacant posts in government schools will be filled. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Teacher Appointment","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-097","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Artificial Intelligence training for Teachers","desc":"To enable government school teachers to effectively learn Artificial Intelligence technology, an Artificial Intelligence and Digital Education Skill Development Scheme will be implemented.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Artificial Intelligence training","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-098","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Removal of Non-Teaching Duties","desc":"The involvement of government school teachers in non-teaching-learning duties will be completely stopped.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Removal of Non-Teaching","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-099","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Salary Hike","desc":"All Anganwadi workers will be converted into 'Grade D' government employees, and on that basis, a salary of 18,000 rupees per month will be provided to them. Similarly, it will be ensured that the monthly salary for Anganwadi assistants and ASHA workers who…","metric":"18,000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Salary Hike","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-100","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Retirement Benefit","desc":"It will be ensured that Anganwadi and ASHA workers who have completed 20 years of service receive 15 lakh rupees as retirement benefit. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"15 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Retirement Benefit","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-101","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Sanitation Worker Training","desc":"Workers who were hitherto involved in the duty of removing human waste will be given training to operate the aforementioned modern machinery and will be appointed as operators. Through this, their loss of job will be prevented, and their dignified life will…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Sanitation Worker Training","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-102","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Pension Scheme","desc":"A pension of 4,000 rupees per month will be provided to sanitation workers who retire from service.","metric":"4,000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Pension Scheme","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-103","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Driver Welfare Board","desc":"A Driver Welfare Board will be established to protect the welfare of registered Auto-Taxi drivers. Life insurance worth 10 lakh rupees and accident insurance worth 10 lakh rupees will be provided to them. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"10 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Driver Welfare Board","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-104","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Digital System Permit","desc":"Procedures including renewal of permits for drivers’ vehicles, renewal of licenses, and renewal of insurance will be completely digitized.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Digital System Permit","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-105","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Taxi App","desc":"A 'Tamil Taxi App' will be introduced in important cities of Tamil Nadu. No fees including platform commission will be collected from drivers for this.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Taxi App","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-106","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Green Motor Vehicle Scheme","desc":"To protect the environment, a 50 percent subsidy (up to 75,000 rupees) will be provided for newly purchased electric autos. A 50 percent subsidy (up to 30,000 rupees) will be provided for converting autos currently in use to the CNG (gas) system.","metric":"75,000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Green Motor Vehicle","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-107","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Best Driver Award","desc":"Driver’s Day will be announced with the aim of honoring drivers. On that day, a state government award and a reward of 50 thousand rupees will be given to drivers who act honestly.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Best Driver Award","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-108","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Nadu Gig Worker Act","desc":"More than 15 lakh gig workers in Tamil Nadu are working independently without any kind of job security or medical insurance facility. Considering their welfare, a Tamil Nadu Gig Worker Act will be enacted, and their social status including job security will…","metric":"15 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Gig","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-109","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Social Security","desc":"Life insurance worth 10 lakh rupees and accident insurance worth 10 lakh rupees will be provided to all registered gig workers. Interest-free loan to buy E-bike Interest-free loans will be provided for gig workers working in companies like Swiggy and Zomato…","metric":"10 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Social Security","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-110","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Street Vending Regularization and Livelihood Protection Act","desc":"Under the Street Vending Regularization and Livelihood Protection Act, special zones for street vending will be established in every urban local body. Up to 50 thousand rupees will be provided to them as investment loan without interest through cooperative …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Street Vending Regularization","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-111","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Tamil Nadu Lawyer Welfare Fund","desc":"3 thousand rupees per month will be provided as pension to lawyers with more than 20 years of practice experience whose annual income is less than 5 lakh. Life insurance will be provided to all registered lawyers.","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Lawyer","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-112","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Legal Consultants Honorarium Fund","desc":"An honorarium fund of 5000 rupees per month will be provided with the aim of honoring legal consultants who provide free legal advice and legal help to rural people. Aram (virtue) Thoon 02","metric":"5000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Legal Consultants Honorarium","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-113","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Restructuring the Construction Worker Welfare Board","desc":"The defects in the welfare board established considering the welfare of construction workers will be removed, and it will be restructured to function fully.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Restructuring the Construction","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-114","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Palmyra Tree Protection","desc":"The Palmyra tree, which serves as the state tree of the Tamil Nadu government and one of the cultural identities of Tamil life, is becoming scarce. To reclaim it, the following schemes will be implemented. The Palmyra tree will be announced as a protected t…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Palmyra Tree Protection","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t2-115","thoon":2,"pillar":"aram","title":"Monsoon Relief for Salt Pan Workers","desc":"The monsoon relief amount provided to salt pan workers will be increased to 7 thousand rupees. [Section Divider: PORUL] Porul (wealth/economy)","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Monsoon Relief for","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t3-116","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Women's Welfare and Safety System","desc":"An exclusive wing for the safety and welfare of adult women and girl children will be established under the direct monitoring of the Chief Minister. Under this wing, everything including welfare schemes and safety features for women and girl children will b…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Women's Welfare and","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-117","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Valueable Women Scheme","desc":"Until they reach 60 years of age, 2500 rupees will be credited every month to the bank account of every female family head. Through this, the state where female family heads depend on others for their basic expenses will change and their economic freedom wi…","metric":"2500 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Valueable Women Scheme","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-118","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Annapoorani Super Six","desc":"The amount for buying 6 gas cylinders per year for every family will be paid directly into their bank accounts.","metric":"","scheme":"Annapoorani Super Six","short":"Annapoorani Super Six","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-119","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Vettri Payanam (Victorious Journey)","desc":"Currently, women's free travel is in practice only in specific government buses. Changing this state, the Vettri Payanam scheme, where women travel without charge in all urban, city, and inter-district government buses operating throughout the state, will b…","metric":"","scheme":"Vettri Payanam (Victorious Journey)","short":"Vettri Payanam (Victorious","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-120","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Annan Seer (Elder Brother’s Gift) Scheme","desc":"8 grams (1 sovereign) of gold and a silk saree will be provided for brides in marriages taking place in families with an annual income of less than 5 lakh. Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 03","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"Annan Seer (Elder Brother’s Gift) Scheme","short":"Annan Seer (Elder","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-121","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Thaimaman (Maternal Uncle) Gold Ring Scheme","desc":"A gold ring and a Maternal Uncle’s Gift Kit containing essential items including soft cloth and diapers will be provided to every baby born in government hospitals in Tamil Nadu.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Thaimaman (Maternal Uncle)","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-122","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Kamarajar Education Guarantee Scheme","desc":"15 thousand rupees per year will be credited in two installments to the bank account of the mother/guardian of students studying from first standard to twelfth standard in government and government-aided schools. Through this, the state where students drop …","metric":"","scheme":"Kamarajar Education Guarantee Scheme","short":"Kamarajar Education Guarantee","personas":["youth","woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-123","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Widow and Destitute Women Assistance","desc":"3 thousand rupees will be provided as monthly assistance to widows and destitute women suffering in poverty.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Widow and Destitute","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-124","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Singa Pengal (Lioness) Development Scheme","desc":"Interest-free loans up to 5 lakh rupees will be provided to women's self-help groups. 5 lakh rupees will be provided as investment subsidy, in a way that does not require repayment, to women's self-help groups attempting to become small-micro entrepreneurs.…","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"Singa Pengal (Lioness) Development Scheme","short":"Singa Pengal (Lioness)","personas":["business","woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-125","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Magalir Mahasakthi (Women’s Great Power)","desc":"Food products, linen varieties, and products required for schools required for government institutions and government service institutions are currently procured from many private companies. Changing this state, 40 percent of such procured products will be …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Magalir Mahasakthi (Women’s","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-126","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Special Industrial Estates","desc":"Special industrial estates with infrastructures that fully fulfill the requirements of women will be established in 10 cities: Chennai, Coimbatore, Madurai, Trichy, Salem, Vellore, Tiruppur, Thanjavur, Thoothukudi, and Tirunelveli. Porul (wealth/economy) Th…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Special Industrial Estates","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-127","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Women's Welfare","desc":"C. Uncompromising Women's Safety","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Women's Welfare","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-128","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Rani Velu Nachiyar Force","desc":"To improve women's safety, 500 monitoring groups functioning in the name of Rani Velu Nachiyar will be established in Tamil Nadu. These groups, formed entirely by women, will undertake monitoring duties in plain clothes, with cameras fitted on their bodies.","metric":"","scheme":"Rani Velu Nachiyar Force","short":"Rani Velu Nachiyar","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-129","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Integrated Monitoring Center functioning with Artificial Intelligence technology","desc":"The Kavalan App currently in practice for women's safety will be improved, and a 'Smart Panic Button' will be established in all vehicles including buses and share autos operating throughout Tamil Nadu. This will be connected with Artificial Intelligence te…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Integrated Monitoring Center","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-130","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Special Fast-track Courts for Women","desc":"Special fast-track courts will be established to investigate crimes against women and provide justice quickly.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Special Fast-track Courts","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-131","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Hostels for Working Women and Female Students","desc":"Hostels with appropriate safety and modern facilities for working women and female students to stay will be established in important cities throughout Tamil Nadu. In this, only 2500 rupees will be collected as the maximum monthly fee. Porul (wealth/economy)…","metric":"2500 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Hostels for Working","personas":["youth","woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-132","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Pregnancy Assistance","desc":"A financial aid of 25 thousand rupees will be provided for pregnant women to help them buy necessary nutritious foods, perform monthly medical check-ups, and fulfill essential requirements. Service and help centers for pregnant women will be established thr…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Pregnancy Assistance","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-133","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Sanitary Napkins without cost","desc":"Sanitary napkins without cost will be provided to women in ration shops, schools, and colleges. Sanitary napkin vending machines will be established in important places in every town. Arrangements will be made in all government school toilets to formally di…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Sanitary Napkins without","personas":["youth","woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-134","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Free Cervical Cancer Screening and Vaccine","desc":"HPV vaccines will be administered to all girls aged 9 to 14 without charge. Furthermore, in primary health centers throughout Tamil Nadu, free cervical cancer screening will be performed for all women over 30 years of age.","metric":"30 years","scheme":"","short":"Free Cervical Cancer","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t3-135","thoon":3,"pillar":"porul","title":"Solar Stoves for Tribal Women","desc":"To reduce the difficulties in using wood stoves for tribal and hill-dwelling women, solar stoves without cost will be provided. Porul (wealth/economy)","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Solar Stoves for","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t4-136","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Youth Victory Fund","desc":"A monthly assistance of 4 thousand rupees will be provided to unemployed graduates who have registered in the employment office and are waiting. A monthly assistance of 2500 rupees will be provided to youth who have completed 12th standard, ITI, etc., inclu…","metric":"2500 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Youth Victory Fund","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-137","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Transparency in Employment","desc":"A special act will be enacted to ensure that appointments made for government jobs take place in an honest manner and with transparency. Through this act, all procedures from vacancy announcement to job appointments will be completed within one year.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Transparency in Employment","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-138","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Filling Vacancies","desc":"All vacancies in government departments will be quickly filled.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Filling Vacancies","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-139","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Education Guarantee Scheme","desc":"A collateral-free (Collateral Free) loan up to 20 lakh rupees will be provided to all students studying from bachelor's degree (UG) to research degree (PhD). Through this, it will be ensured that students study the courses they desire in the colleges they d…","metric":"20 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Education Guarantee Scheme","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-140","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Vettri Industrial Training","desc":"Internship training will be provided in coordination with government and private industrial companies to improve youth skills. It will be ensured that 5 lakh youth benefit through this initiative every year. During this training period, 10 thousand rupees p…","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"Vettri Industrial Training","short":"Vettri Industrial Training","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-141","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Vettri Entrepreneur Scheme","desc":"A collateral-free (Collateral Free) loan up to 25 lakh rupees will be provided on behalf of the government to youth who desire to start a business. Through this, the dream of becoming an entrepreneur for numerous youth will come true.","metric":"25 lakh","scheme":"Vettri Entrepreneur Scheme","short":"Vettri Entrepreneur Scheme","personas":["business","youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-142","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Our Town Our Job Employment Scheme","desc":"Private companies that employ Tamil Nadu youth up to 70 percent in their institutions will be provided a 2.5% subsidy in State GST tax, a 5% subsidy in electricity charges, and priority in government procurement. Through this scheme, it will be ensured that…","metric":"2.5%","scheme":"","short":"Our Town Our","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-143","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Chief Minister's People's Service Friend Scheme","desc":"Under the Chief Minister's People's Service Friend scheme, 5 lakh youth will be appointed as permanent workers in every Gram Panchayat and urban local body, and a monthly salary of 18,000 rupees will be provided to them. These workers will ensure that all s…","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Chief Minister's People's","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-144","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Digital Creator Incentive Scheme","desc":"The following schemes will be implemented with the aim of encouraging creators who take the prides of Tamil land's history, art, heritage, language, food, music, etc., to the world level on digital platforms. One and a half lakh creators will be selected an…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Digital Creator Incentive","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-145","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu Youth Advisory Council","desc":"To ensure the contribution of youth in Tamil Nadu government policy and administrative decisions, a Tamil Nadu Youth Advisory Council will be created. This council will directly communicate its opinions and advice to the Chief Minister and other important s…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Youth","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-146","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Micro Tech Park (Micro Industrial Parks)","desc":"Micro tech parks will be established in 25 towns including Pollachi, Karur, Kovilpatti, Krishnagiri, Thiruvannamalai, Vellore, Erode, Dindigul, Namakkal, and Sivakasi. Every micro tech park will be established with infrastructure facilities including high-s…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Micro Tech Park","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-147","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Youth Welfare","desc":"B. Tamil Nadu Standing Tall in Sports","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Youth Welfare","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-148","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu Sports University","desc":"A Tamil Nadu Sports University will be established with medical facilities for sports players, technology for sports, and excellent administrative structures to provide high-caliber sports training to the extent of converting Tamil Nadu sports players into …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Sports","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-149","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu Vettri Olympic Scheme","desc":"To change Tamil Nadu into the sports capital of India, a Tamil Nadu Olympic Skill Development Scheme will be introduced. Through this, talented players throughout Tamil Nadu will be identified and international standard training will be provided to the exte…","metric":"","scheme":"Tamil Nadu Vettri Olympic Scheme","short":"Tamil Nadu Vettri","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-150","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"World-class Sports Infrastructures","desc":"Multi-Sport Stadiums, sports complexes, gymkhanas, sports academies, and training centers of world-class standards will be established in 10 zonal capitals of Tamil Nadu.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"World-class Sports Infrastructures","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-151","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Young Players Identification Scheme","desc":"500 sports players with interest and talent in sports will be identified and selected from schools themselves. World-class training to the extent of winning in Olympic competitions will be provided to those players selected in this way, aged between 8 and 14.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Young Players Identification","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-152","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Paralympics Skill Development Scheme","desc":"Qualified Paralympics players will be identified, and world-class training and financial aid will be provided to them. World-class Paralympics training centers will be established in Madurai, Salem, and Trichy.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Paralympics Skill Development","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t4-153","thoon":4,"pillar":"porul","title":"Maritime Sports","desc":"10 maritime sports centers (Surfing, Kayaking, Wind-Surfing, Snorkelling, Scuba Diving) will be established. Priority will be given to coastal fisher youth to receive training in these sports centers. Porul (wealth/economy)","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Maritime Sports","personas":["fisher","youth","all"]},{"id":"t5-154","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Agricultural Loan Waiver","desc":"Crop loans taken in cooperative banks by farmers holding less than 5 acres of land will be completely waived. 50 percent of crop loans taken in cooperative banks by farmers holding more than 5 acres of land will be waived.","metric":"5 acres","scheme":"","short":"Agricultural Loan Waiver","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-155","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Vettri Farmer Rights Amount","desc":"As sowing-time financial aid, 15 thousand rupees per year will be provided in two installments (July - August season, January-February season) to the family of every farmer holding their own agricultural land. This finance will be helpful to manage sowing-t…","metric":"","scheme":"Vettri Farmer Rights Amount","short":"Vettri Farmer Rights","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-156","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Ulavar Thozhar (Farmer Friend) Scheme","desc":"A method of introducing Farmer License Cards for lease farmers and agricultural laborers will be introduced. An assistance of 10 thousand rupees per year will be directly paid into the bank accounts of farmers holding this license card.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Ulavar Thozhar (Farmer","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-157","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Guaranteed Minimum Support Price for Paddy-Sugarcane","desc":"3500 rupees per quintal for paddy and 4500 rupees per ton for sugarcane will be provided as the minimum support price. When a decline occurs in the market price of turmeric, sugarcane, paddy, and milling copra, the government will also accept that loss. All…","metric":"3500 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Guaranteed Minimum Support","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-158","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Farmers Income Hike Commission","desc":"A Farmers Income Hike Commission will be established to find advice to increase farmers' income, simple marketing methods, and guidelines related to price determination. This will provide recommendations to the government regarding the aforementioned every …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Farmers Income Hike","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-159","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"100% Percent Crop Insurance","desc":"To benefit farmers, additional Agro-meteorological science centers will be established throughout Tamil Nadu. Through this, the loss of crops affected during monsoon seasons will be accurately calculated. On that basis, compensation will be quickly provided…","metric":"100%","scheme":"","short":"100% Percent Crop","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-160","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Copra Farmers Welfare","desc":"Copra support funds will be allocated in a way that price changes in coconuts do not affect coconut farmers. Milling copras will be procured through coconut producers' cooperative societies in places like Coimbatore, Thanjavur, Pollachi, and Kangeyam. Oil w…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Copra Farmers Welfare","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-161","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu Organic Farming Scheme","desc":"The following actions will be taken to change Tamil Nadu into a leading state in organic farming. A monthly assistance of two thousand rupees will be provided for the first three years to farmers who convert from synthetic fertilizer agriculture to organic …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Organic","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-162","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Farmer Producer Organization","desc":"An incentive of 5000 rupees will be provided to encourage farmers who join Farmer Producer Organizations. Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 05","metric":"5000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Farmer Producer Organization","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-163","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Free Higher Education for Farmers' Children","desc":"Free higher education will be provided to the children of farmers holding less than two acres of agricultural land.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Free Higher Education","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-164","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Reducing Wastage of Produce at Procurement Centers","desc":"All procurement centers, cluster hubs, and silos, including those for paddy and other procured produce, vegetables, food grains, and spices, will be formally handled and protected. Through this, post-harvest losses will be reduced. Accurate weighing and sto…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Reducing Wastage of","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-165","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Farmers, Agricultural Laborers and Fishermen Welfare","desc":"B. Fishermen Welfare","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Farmers, Agricultural Laborers","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-166","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Fishermen Protection Rights Amount","desc":"The fishing ban period relief amount will be increased to 20 thousand rupees. A North-East monsoon relief amount of 7000 rupees will be provided to fishermen who do fishing as a traditional industry.","metric":"7000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Fishermen Protection Rights","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-167","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Fishermen Accident Insurance","desc":"Accident insurance worth 25 lakh rupees will be provided to every registered fisherman. Furthermore, sea ambulances functioning with satellite technology to help fishermen struggling for their lives, having been caught in accidents at sea, will be establish…","metric":"25 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Fishermen Accident Insurance","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-168","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Fishermen Fuel Protection","desc":"The diesel subsidy for fishing boats will be increased from 1800 liters to 3600 liters. Additionally, a subsidy of 15 rupees per liter will be directly credited into the boat owner’s bank account.","metric":"15 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Fishermen Fuel Protection","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-169","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Minimum Support Price for Fish","desc":"For the first time in India, a minimum support price will be determined for Shrimp, Sardine, Mackerel, and Squid. To avoid fishermen being affected by the price decline that occurs when these fish come to the market in large quantities, the deficit amount w…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Minimum Support Price","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-170","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Kadal Thai (Sea Mother) House","desc":"A coastal residential scheme will be created to ensure the creation of coastlines without huts. The houses built under this scheme will be built with a quality to face storms, sea erosion, and bad weather. Priority will be given in this scheme to the fisher…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Kadal Thai (Sea","personas":["woman","fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-171","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Fishermen Entrepreneur Welfare Scheme","desc":"An investment subsidy of 5 lakh rupees will be provided to fisher youth who desire to become entrepreneurs in value-added maritime industries like boat repair workshop, sea food export company, fish processing industry, and seaweed production.","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Fishermen Entrepreneur Welfare","personas":["business","youth","fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-172","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Local Water Body Fishermen Welfare","desc":"Fishermen who fish in rivers, kanmais, ponds, and dams, excluding the sea, do not receive any of the benefits of the Tamil Nadu Fishermen Welfare Board. Changing this state, provisions will be made so that all benefits of the Tamil Nadu Fishermen Welfare Bo…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Local Water Body","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-173","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Sea Product Sales Outlet","desc":"Just as there are Aavin sales outlets to sell dairy products, separate sales outlets will be established throughout Tamil Nadu to sell maritime food products, with the aim of improving fishermen's economy. In these, maritime food products including value-ad…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Sea Product Sales","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-174","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Seaweed Park","desc":"A seaweed processing industrial park will be established in Rameswaram. Here, seaweeds will be converted into food, fertilizer, and beauty products. In this, priority will be given to women of women's self-help groups.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Seaweed Park","personas":["woman","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-175","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Sea Gold Protection Scheme","desc":"Barriers will be established for a length of 200 km in coastal districts like Nagapattinam, Cuddalore, Villupuram, Ramanathapuram, and Kanyakumari which are most affected by sea erosion.","metric":"200 km","scheme":"","short":"Sea Gold Protection","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-176","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Fishing Harbor Improvement","desc":"Structures including cold storage warehouses to keep fish preserved, facilities to convert toxic waste into useful fish feed (Bio Floc Technology), and cage fish farming will be created in fishing harbors throughout Tamil Nadu. A commercial chain without in…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Fishing Harbor Improvement","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-177","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Deep Sea Boat Financial Loan","desc":"Interest-free loans will be provided to fishermen to buy deep sea fishing boats with modern processing facilities. Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 05","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Deep Sea Boat","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-178","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"River Linking","desc":"The river linking schemes of Cauvery-Vaigai-Gundar, Thenpennaiyaru-Palar, Pennaiyaru-Cheyyaru, and Thamirabarani-Vaipparu have all been announced and still remain without being fully implemented. To implement them immediately, 5000 crore rupees will be allo…","metric":"5000 crore","scheme":"","short":"River Linking","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-179","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Neeratchi (Water Governance) Scheme","desc":"More than 39 thousand irrigation tanks throughout Tamil Nadu are in a poor state without formal maintenance. All these will be restructured under the Neeratchi scheme. Through this, 5 lakh new agricultural ponds will be established.","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Neeratchi (Water Governance)","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-180","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Striving to reach 100% Irrigation Area","desc":"Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam will have the goal of reaching 100% irrigation area throughout Tamil Nadu by converting rain-fed lands, which depend only on rain, into விளைநிலங்கள் (cultivated lands) with irrigation facilities. A special mission (Special Mission) …","metric":"100%","scheme":"","short":"Striving to reach","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-181","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Drop-by-Drop Water Scheme","desc":"The 75 percent subsidy currently in practice for small-micro farmers to install drip and sprinkler irrigation will be increased to 90 percent. Through this, the drawing of groundwater for agriculture will decrease by 40 percent. The declining agricultural a…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Drop-by-Drop Water Scheme","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-182","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Accelerating Irrigation Schemes","desc":"To ensure irrigation safety, groundwater enrichment, and drought prevention capacity throughout Tamil Nadu, Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam will implement a special scheme (Mission-mode programme) to quickly implement zonal-wise water infrastructure schemes. This …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Accelerating Irrigation Schemes","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-183","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Copra Farmers Welfare (Context: Solar Pump Sets)","desc":"In the next 5 years, diesel and electric pump sets will be converted into solar pump sets. The electricity that becomes surplus in this will be sold to the electricity board and the revenue coming through it will be provided to the farmers.","metric":"5 years","scheme":"","short":"Copra Farmers Welfare","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-184","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Ulavan (Farmer) Artificial Intelligence Scheme","desc":"To provide every farmer with information including the nature of his land, the pesticide impact in it, nutrient deficiency, on which day to sow, and to harvest, an Artificial Intelligence technology facility will be provided on the smart phones they use. Th…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Ulavan (Farmer) Artificial","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-185","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Agricultural Business Centers","desc":"Agricultural business protection centers will be established in places including Coimbatore, Madurai, and Trichy. An investment subsidy of 10 lakh rupees will be provided to agricultural business entrepreneurs who start start-up companies in agricultural bu…","metric":"10 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Agricultural Business Centers","personas":["business","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-186","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Turmeric, Mango, Copra Value-Addition Centers!","desc":"To obtain higher prices for the Erode turmeric, Krishnagiri mango, and copra produced in the Kongu region that Tamil Nadu farmers produce, they will be value-added. A turmeric extraction park will be established in Erode, and through it, high-quality turmer…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Turmeric, Mango, Copra","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-187","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Cauvery Delta Environmental Restoration","desc":"The Cauvery Delta basin serves as the heart of Tamil Nadu's agriculture. But, due to environmental degradations, the water resources, land resources, and agricultural production of the Cauvery Delta basin have met with great impact. To rectify that, the fol…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Cauvery Delta Environmental","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-188","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Coastline Horticulture Scheme","desc":"'Blue-Green Horticulture Parks' with solar electricity facility will be established in coastal districts including Ramanathapuram, Nagapattinam, and Thoothukudi. Through these, the increased salt content in the water of coastal districts will be removed. Th…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Coastline Horticulture Scheme","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-189","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Delta Bio-Purification Center","desc":"During every rice harvest that takes place in Tamil Nadu, tons of straw are obtained. But, they are mostly burned without being formally used; or removed as agricultural waste. Changing this state, a scheme to prepare fuel gas from straw will be implemented…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Delta Bio-Purification Center","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-190","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Drought Zones!","desc":"Ramanathapuram and Virudhunagar districts will be announced as drought zones. In these drought zones, incentives will be provided to farmers who produce millets and oilseeds using less water through drip irrigation and sprinkler irrigation methods.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Drought Zones!","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-191","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Refrigerated Storage Warehouses","desc":"With the aim of preventing agricultural produce from being wasted on a large scale after harvest, quality refrigerated storage warehouses will be established. Furthermore, appropriate actions will also be undertaken to make formal packing facilities to prot…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Refrigerated Storage Warehouses","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-192","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Milk Procurement Price Hike","desc":"The procurement price for the milk that the Aavin company buys from milk producers will be increased to 44 rupees per liter.","metric":"44 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Milk Procurement Price","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-193","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"A2 Milk Incentive Scheme","desc":"Actions will be undertaken to increase the production of A2 category milk, which is obtained only from our native cows through Aavin, and to increase the production of food products prepared from it like ghee, cheese, and ice cream, and to market them in a …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"A2 Milk Incentive","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-194","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Insurance for Livestock","desc":"A complete insurance scheme for livestock will be provided without any charge to families below the poverty line who are involved in livestock rearing. Furthermore, actions will also be taken to provide appropriate incentives to those families.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Insurance for Livestock","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-195","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Traditional Livestock Breed Recovery","desc":"To reclaim the traditional cattle breeds of Tamil Nadu—Kangeyam, Pulikulam, Umbalachery, Bargur, and Alambadi cattle breeds—an assistance of 5000 rupees will be provided as livestock assistance to women of self-help groups who rear them. Livestock banks wil…","metric":"5000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Traditional Livestock Breed","personas":["woman","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-196","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Livestock Fodder Bank","desc":"Fodder banks to store and sell fodder for livestock, and refrigerated facilities to store milk will be created on a massive scale at every Gram Panchayat level.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Livestock Fodder Bank","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t5-197","thoon":5,"pillar":"porul","title":"Livestock Medical Centers","desc":"Veterinary hospitals will be created in necessary numbers throughout Tamil Nadu, with appropriate staff. Similarly, veterinary multi-specialty hospitals will be established in suburban districts. Porul (wealth/economy)","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Livestock Medical Centers","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t6-198","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Modernizing Government Schools","desc":"In every government school of Tamil Nadu, science laboratories of world-class standards, computer laboratories with high-speed internet facility, modern libraries encompassing digital sections, STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Maths) teaching centers…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Modernizing Government Schools","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-199","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Changing into the Leading State in Learning Outcomes","desc":"Special schemes will be formulated and implemented in full swing to remove gender and social-based deficiencies in students' learning ability. Through this, Tamil Nadu will be changed into the first state in the country in learning outcomes (Learning Outcom…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Changing into the","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-200","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Kamarajar Special Schools","desc":"100 excellence schools will be opened throughout Tamil Nadu for students belonging to families that are socially and economically backward who excel in education. In these schools, education, food, residence, textbooks, and uniforms will be provided without…","metric":"","scheme":"Kamarajar Special Schools","short":"Kamarajar Special Schools","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-201","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"0% Dropout","desc":"To prevent the increasing dropout of school students, monitoring systems will be created throughout Tamil Nadu with the help of Artificial Intelligence technology. 1000 education coordinators will be appointed to identify students who drop out of school edu…","metric":"0%","scheme":"","short":"0% Dropout","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-202","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Breakfast Scheme Expansion","desc":"The Chief Minister's Breakfast Scheme will be expanded up to 8th standard to government schools and government-aided schools, and nutritious breakfast will be provided. Through this scheme, it will be ensured that all students receive balanced nutrition.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Breakfast Scheme Expansion","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-203","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"10 Percent Reservation","desc":"The 7.5 percent reservation for government school students in bachelor's degree studies will be increased to 10 percent. Furthermore, a 10 percent reservation will also be provided for government school students in master's degree studies.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"10 Percent Reservation","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-204","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Head Teacher Skill Development Scheme","desc":"A Head Teacher Skill Development Scheme will be implemented with the aim of further sharpening the leadership qualities of school head teachers. An exclusive leadership training station will be established for this, and training will be provided continuousl…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Head Teacher Skill","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-205","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu Student Entrepreneur Scheme","desc":"To encourage entrepreneurship among students during their school years, 5,100 rupees will be provided as investment fund to students studying in 11th and 12th standards in government schools under the Tamil Nadu Student Entrepreneur Scheme. This fund will b…","metric":"5,100 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Student","personas":["business","youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-206","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Student Mental Health Protection","desc":"To ensure the mental health and safety of government school students and teachers, 5,000 mental health consultants will be appointed and psychological first-aid training will be provided to students and teachers. A happiness curriculum will be introduced to…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Student Mental Health","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-207","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Artificial Intelligence section in School Curriculum","desc":"To change Tamil Nadu government school students into pioneer students, Artificial Intelligence science will be taught in the curriculum from 6th standard to 12th standard. Furthermore, sensing the changing time and environment, climate science will also be …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Artificial Intelligence section","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-208","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"New Government Professional Colleges","desc":"Five new engineering colleges and three medical colleges will be started in districts without government professional colleges. Efforts to insist the Union government to provide permission for medical colleges will be undertaken. Thirty government arts and …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"New Government Professional","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-209","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Education Life Fund","desc":"8,000 rupees will be provided to every government school student who completes school studies and joins a government college, with the aim of reducing the economic burden caused by college admission expenses.","metric":"8,000 rupees","scheme":"","short":"Education Life Fund","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-210","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"First Honor to Intellect","desc":"The government itself will accept the education and living expenses of Tamil Nadu students who qualify to study in the world's top 100 educational institutions. In return, those students, after completing their degree, will function for three years as gover…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"First Honor to","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-211","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"College Fee Waiver for First-Generation Students","desc":"College fees will be completely waived for first-generation students belonging to Adi Dravidar and Tribal communities and first-generation students belonging to economically backward families who study in government schools and subsequently join and study i…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"College Fee Waiver","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-212","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Exclusive University for Emerging Technologies","desc":"For emerging technologies such as Artificial Intelligence, Quantum Computing, Biotech, Climate Tech, Space Tech, and Cyber Security: Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 06","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Exclusive University for","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-213","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"ITI Modernization","desc":"ITIs throughout Tamil Nadu will be modernized and curricula under the new sections of Augmented Reality (AR), Virtual Reality (VR), Artificial Intelligence (AI), and Machine Learning (ML) will be added. New ITIs will be opened as per the students' requirement.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"ITI Modernization","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-214","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"World-Class Education","desc":"C. Training for Competitive Exams","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"World-Class Education","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-215","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Skill Training Centers for Emerging Technologies","desc":"Skill training centers for emerging technologies will be established in every district of Tamil Nadu, and free six-month certificate courses will be taught in sections like Artificial Intelligence, EV technology, Animation, Cloud Computing, and Cyber Securi…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Skill Training Centers","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t6-216","thoon":6,"pillar":"porul","title":"Free Training for Competitive Exams","desc":"The following actions will be undertaken for rural youth to excel in competitive exams. Every district library will be modernized and high-quality training centers for competitive exams will be established there. The learning ability of every youth will be …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Free Training for","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t7-217","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"1.5 Trillion Dollar Economy","desc":"A goal will be determined to raise Tamil Nadu's economy to 1.5 trillion dollars by the year 2036, and necessary initiatives will be taken. Through this, it will be ensured that the state's decade-long growth is like never before.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"1.5 Trillion Dollar","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-218","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Top 20 Scheme","desc":"20 sectors that are at the forefront of industrial growth and have the chance to grow at high speed in the future will be selected and exclusive action plans (Industry Transformation Maps) will be formulated for those sectors. Industrial growth centers will…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Top 20 Scheme","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-219","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Globalizing Tamil Nadu Industrial Institutions","desc":"There is a welcome throughout the world for the products produced in Tamil Nadu, such as the textiles prepared in Tiruppur, leather products prepared in Vellore, spare parts produced in Chennai, and jewelry created in Erode. Therefore, an industrial institu…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Globalizing Tamil Nadu","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-220","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"SIPCOT and Industrial Estate Reform, Modernization and Land Use","desc":"To make it easy to do business and to improve export capacity: Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 07","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"SIPCOT and Industrial","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-221","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Wealthy Tamil Nadu","desc":"B. Micro-Small-Medium Enterprise Renaissance","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Wealthy Tamil Nadu","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-222","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Security Loan Assistance Scheme - 15 Thousand Crore Loan Assistance","desc":"Micro-small-medium enterprises in Tamil Nadu have been encountering instability due to electricity charge hike, improper distribution facilities, and economic crises. To prevent this, 15,000 crore rupees of state finance will be allocated to provide loan as…","metric":"15,000 crore","scheme":"","short":"Security Loan Assistance","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-223","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Electricity Guarantee Scheme","desc":"The hike in electricity fixed charges (Fixed Charges) and peak-hour electricity use charges (Peak-hour charges) for micro, small and medium industrial institutions (MSMEs) will be immediately stayed. Furthermore, electricity charges will be regularized afte…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Electricity Guarantee Scheme","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-224","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Technology Upgradation Fund Assistance Scheme","desc":"Micro-small-medium industrial institutions in Tamil Nadu do not buy and use technologies as per the growing world. Specifically, they are without financial facility to buy AI, sensor technology, and modern production machinery. Due to this, the state of Tam…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Technology Upgradation Fund","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-225","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Priority to Tamil Nadu Institutions","desc":"Out of the products the government procures from small-micro-medium industrial institutions, 40 percent will be procured from institutions belonging to Tamil Nadu. To facilitate this, a Tamil Nadu Supplier Register, which registers the small-micro-medium in…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Priority to Tamil","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-226","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"License in 21 Days","desc":"To improve industrial growth, the difficult procedures for starting industrial institutions will be simplified as follows. * License will be provided in 7 working days to start micro-industries and cottage industries. * License will be provided in 15 workin…","metric":"21 Days","scheme":"","short":"License in 21","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-227","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Investor Promotion Commission","desc":"With the aim of ensuring that foreign investments of multinational companies come to Tamil Nadu on a large scale, a Tamil Nadu Investor Promotion Commission will be created under the Chief Secretary of the Tamil Nadu government. The Industries Secretary wil…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Investor Promotion Commission","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-228","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Non-Resident Tamil Investment Scheme","desc":"To encourage non-resident Tamils as well in Tamil Nadu, the following actions will be undertaken. * The Global Tamil Welfare and Investment Commission will be brought under the direct control of the Chief Minister, and welfare scheme aids for non-resident T…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Non-Resident Tamil Investment","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-229","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"AI Economic Plan","desc":"It is calculated that by the year 2035, India's economy will additionally increase by up to 1.7 trillion US dollars through AI technology. An AI industrial growth plan will be implemented in a way that Tamils also benefit from this. In it, the following ini…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"AI Economic Plan","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-230","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"India's First AI Ministry","desc":"India's first AI Ministry will be started, and a primary AI official will be appointed in every government department on behalf of that ministry. This ministry will advance AI technology initiatives.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"India's First AI","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-231","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Free AI service for Tamil Nadu Entrepreneurs","desc":"An India-first government-owned Ultra High Performance GPU Compute Cluster will be created. Start-up and small-micro-medium institutions in Tamil Nadu can use this facility for AI services without charge.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Free AI service","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-232","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Arivagam AI City","desc":"An exclusive city for AI named 'Arivagam' (House of Wisdom) will be created for the first time in India. Facilities including an AI University, an international skill center, a semiconductor hardware testing lab, and modern residences will feature in it. Po…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Arivagam AI City","personas":["youth","business","all"]},{"id":"t7-233","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Backward District Development Budget","desc":"The per capita income of developed districts in Tamil Nadu is three times higher than the per capita income of backward districts. The reason for this is that a budget with schemes encompassing the development of all districts has not been announced. Changi…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Backward District Development","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-234","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"District Special Industrial Development Scheme","desc":"Under this scheme, a District Special Industrial Development Scheme will be implemented in all 38 districts in consultation with the respective district industrial organizations, sectoral experts, and people's representatives. Under this scheme, 23 thousand…","metric":"38 districts","scheme":"","short":"District Special Industrial","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-235","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Kurinji Zone: Nilgiris-Kodaikanal (Dindigul)","desc":"Although there are abundant natural resources and human resources in the Nilgiris - Kodaikanal hilly areas, there are no formal plans to use them for the economic rise of the people of those areas. To change this, the following actions will be undertaken. *…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Kurinji Zone: Nilgiris-Kodaikanal","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-236","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Start-Smart Tamil Nadu","desc":"Under this scheme, investment help up to 50 lakh, necessary training, appropriate advice and guidelines, and extensive business support will be provided to 10 thousand start-up institutions in 5 years in Tamil Nadu.","metric":"50 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Start-Smart Tamil Nadu","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-237","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"5 International Standard Incubators","desc":"Incubators will be established in districts: Chennai, Coimbatore, Madurai, Trichy, and Salem. Through these, free workspace, investor contact, ultra-modern equipment, legal help, and advice for export will be provided to entrepreneurs.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"5 International Standard","personas":["youth","business","all"]},{"id":"t7-238","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Venture Capital Fund for Start-up institutions","desc":"A 500 crore rupee Venture Capital Fund will be provided on behalf of the government for AI, Deep-Tech, and FinTech start-up institutions. An independent commission consisting of industrial experts will be established to manage this.","metric":"500 crore","scheme":"","short":"Venture Capital Fund","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-239","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu Start-up Conference","desc":"A Tamil Nadu Start-up Conference will be conducted every year with the aim of coordinating start-up founders, investors, and industrial experts throughout the world. Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 07","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Start-up","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-240","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"EV Vehicles and Battery Preparation","desc":"* 20 thousand public EV Charging Stations by 2031: 20 thousand Fast Charging stations will be established throughout Tamil Nadu by 2031. * Battery Cell Industrial Factories: 20 percent cash subsidy will be provided to institutions establishing massive indus…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"EV Vehicles and","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-241","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"India's First Commercial Drone Route","desc":"Special commercial drone routes will be created in 10 districts of Tamil Nadu. Permission from the police department is not required in these routes to distribute products using drones, spray fertilizers and pesticides in agricultural lands, supervise const…","metric":"10 districts","scheme":"","short":"India's First Commercial","personas":["farmer","business","all"]},{"id":"t7-242","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"India's First Digital Finance Center","desc":"An i-Tamil FinTech Corridor will be established in Coimbatore. 30 percent of the expenses for these FinTech start-ups to establish Cloud Servers will be given back in the first three years. Porul (wealth/economy) Thoon 07","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"India's First Digital","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-243","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Tamil Nadu as World Content Center; AVGC-XR Creative Economy","desc":"A multi-skill digital technology called Extended Reality (XR) which integrates Animation, Visual Effects, Gaming and Comics (AVGC) is a growing sector today. Tamil Nadu possesses significant potential in this. TVK government will raise Tamil Nadu as a world…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu as","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-244","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Space Technology; Kulasekarapattinam Space Research Investment","desc":"As ISRO’s new aircraft launch station is about to be located in Kulasekarapattinam, Thoothukudi district, the TVK government will undertake the following initiatives for Tamil Nadu to change into the primary state in space technology in India. * The Thoothu…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Space Technology; Kulasekarapattinam","personas":["business","all"]},{"id":"t7-245","thoon":7,"pillar":"porul","title":"Green Hydrogen Center at Thoothukudi Port","desc":"Green hydrogen is becoming the primary fuel in the international shipping sector. Due to climate and geological structure, Thoothukudi is an important shipping junction center. As a step in the plan for Thoothukudi to change into the primary port in South A…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Green Hydrogen Center","personas":["youth","business","all"]},{"id":"t8-246","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"People's Welfare Protection; ₹25 lakh Medical Insurance for all families","desc":"An ordinary family has the state of having to spend their lifetime savings exactly for quality medicine. As soon as the TVK government is formed, a ‘People’s Welfare Insurance’ card worth ₹25 lakh will be provided to every family. Treatment can be obtained …","metric":"₹25 lakh","scheme":"","short":"People's Welfare Protection;","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-247","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Full Physical Examination without cost","desc":"A full physical examination without charge will be performed for every person in Tamil Nadu once a year. Through this, people can monitor their physical condition and be cautious from disease components like cancer and sugar.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Full Physical Examination","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-248","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Five New Multi-specialty Hospitals","desc":"Five multi-specialty hospitals containing 500 beds, digital ICU, and modern disease detection facilities will be opened, selecting five backward areas starting from the southern part of Tamil Nadu.","metric":"500 beds","scheme":"","short":"Five New Multi-specialty","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-249","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Modern Primary Health Centers","desc":"All primary health centers will be upgraded to the state of 'IPHS 2025'. Medical staff including three doctors, one lab technician, and one mental health consultant will be ready 24*7.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Modern Primary Health","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-250","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"People's Welfare Center; 3000 Clinics with Tele-medicine","desc":"3,000 People's Welfare Centers will be established with one nurse, tele-medicine facilities to consult with the nearby primary health center, and disease detection instruments. These People's Welfare Centers will function from 7 am to 9 pm throughout the we…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"People's Welfare Center;","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-251","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"IVF Sandhathi (Legacy) Scheme; Treatment for childless couples","desc":"Free IVF (Artificial Insemination) centers will be established in all government district headquarters hospitals and government medical colleges throughout Tamil Nadu. Through this, all treatments related to IVF will be provided for free without charge.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"IVF Sandhathi (Legacy)","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t8-252","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Modernizing Rural Hospitals","desc":"All rural hospitals will be modernized with dialysis units with two beds, emergency treatment units with four beds, pregnancy examination and operation theater, and increased speed ambulances.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Modernizing Rural Hospitals","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-253","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Medicines at Low Prices","desc":"High-grade premium medicines will be available in all government hospitals and medical college hospitals at cheap prices, from 50 percent to 90 percent cheaper than what is available outside.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Medicines at Low","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t8-254","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Happy Tamil Nadu Mission","desc":"To improve mental health, social harmony, and quality of life, the TVK government will create a state-wide ‘happiness ecosystem’ in coordination with large corporations, social organizations, and educational institutions. Through governance centered on meas…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Happy Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-255","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Mental Health Medical Scheme","desc":"Today in Tamil Nadu, mental health medicine remains a greatly unnoticed medical crisis. A mental health consultation medical section with 10 beds will be opened with every community hospital. A mental health consultant will be employed in every high school.…","metric":"10 beds","scheme":"","short":"Mental Health Medical","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-256","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamil Nadu as World Famous Identity in Siddha","desc":"TVK government will formulate a Siddha welfare tourism scheme. A government-recognized Siddha restructuring certificate will be provided. Siddha centers will be established in Ooty, Kodaikanal, Yercaud, and Courtallam. These will be connected with Siddha to…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu as","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-257","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Medicine and Environment","desc":"B. Let's protect the future of Tamil Nadu; Concerns regarding Environment, Forests and Climate Change","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Medicine and Environment","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-258","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamil Nadu Climate Budget ₹3000 crore","desc":"₹3000 crore will be allocated as a climate budget for Tamil Nadu to excel in actions against climate change as mentioned by the UN. This fund, which cannot be used for anything else, will be spent only to take the state towards renewable energy resources an…","metric":"₹3000 crore","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Climate","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-259","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Disaster Management to avoid Death","desc":"High loss of lives occurs because appropriate precautionary actions are not taken against environmental disasters such as storms, floods, and heat waves. Integrated disaster management offices in 38 districts, flood prevention infrastructure in 5 coastal ci…","metric":"38 districts","scheme":"","short":"Disaster Management to","personas":["fisher","all"]},{"id":"t8-260","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Sustainable Energy Economic Wing","desc":"A Sustainable Energy Economic Wing functioning directly under the Chief Minister’s office will be created. A plan will be formulated with fund allocation for climate protection activities such as providing green bonds to grow the economy for sustainable ene…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Sustainable Energy Economic","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-261","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Green Tamil Nadu Scheme; 33% Forests in five years","desc":"TVK government is committed to increasing the area of Tamil Nadu's forests to 33% by the year 2031. Restructuring of sandalwood trees in the Eastern Ghats in coordination with tribal people and economic opportunities arising from it will be regularized. Ins…","metric":"33%","scheme":"","short":"Green Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-262","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Clean Rivers","desc":"As the governments that ruled until now did not follow appropriate climate controls for factories, the three great rivers of Tamil Nadu—Cauvery, Vaigai, and Thamirabarani—have met with destruction. In the TVK government, this will be strictly prevented. The…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Clean Rivers","personas":["farmer","all"]},{"id":"t8-263","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Forests and Humans","desc":"In forests in Nilgiris, Coimbatore, Dharmapuri, Krishnagiri, Salem, and Erode districts, solar energy terminals with 50 km length for tribal people, and 500 forest protection officials with GPS contact vehicles at nights will be involved in protection duty.…","metric":"50 km","scheme":"","short":"Forests and Humans","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-264","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Wetland Forests Protection","desc":"Wetland forests remain as a factor that saved a great number of people from the 2004 tsunami. They will be connected with the forest department and protected as a protection zone.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Wetland Forests Protection","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-265","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Pure Air","desc":"The air pollution measurement of Tamil Nadu reaches a dangerous state at many times. ₹500 crore of finance will be allocated per year to control air pollution, and schemes will be formulated and monitored. Inbam (joy/well-being) Thoon 08","metric":"₹500 crore","scheme":"","short":"Pure Air","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-266","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Cooum and Adyar Rivers Recovery Mission","desc":"Chennai Cooum and Adyar rivers will be reclaimed through a 'mission-mode' (Mission-mode) approach to ensure ecological renaissance and pollution control.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Cooum and Adyar","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t8-267","thoon":8,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Pallikaranai Wetland Protection and Restructuring","desc":"Encroachments in the Pallikaranai wetland will be removed; furthermore, this wetland will be protected and reclaimed as an important urban wetland and biodiversity zone. Inbam (joy/well-being)","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Pallikaranai Wetland Protection","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-268","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"World-Class Infrastructure","desc":"B. Modern Infrastructure Metro Decentralization; Chennai Metro Phase 2, Coimbatore Metro Phase 1 and Madurai Metro Project Draft TVK government will quickly complete Phase 2 of the Chennai Metro Rail with a distance of 118.9 km, and will start and complete …","metric":"9 km","scheme":"","short":"World-Class Infrastructure","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-269","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Railway Link Line Scheme","desc":"Railway link lines in Tamil Nadu are continuously being neglected by Union governments. The Tindivanam Thiruvannamalai line, the Thoothukudi-Madurai line via Aruppukottai, and the fourth line between Tambaram and Chengalpattu have been announced and still r…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Railway Link Line","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-270","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Multi-skill Service Exchange Park","desc":"A multi-skill service exchange park coordinating freight transport and freight protection duties will be established in three places: the Chennai Port-Railway orbital area, at the Coimbatore industrial area site in the West, and in Thoothukudi in the South.…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Multi-skill Service Exchange","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-271","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Roads with Technology and Accident-free Transport","desc":"Traffic irregularities and accidents will be prevented through speed control cameras with AI technology help at technology monitorings and accident areas on Tamil Nadu highways. Individuals like auto, rental car (Cab), and private vehicle owners who help ac…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Roads with Technology","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-272","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Damage-free Highways","desc":"₹20,000 crore of finance is currently allocated per year for Tamil Nadu highways, district and rural roads. But, as roads are still with pits and holes, the state where two-wheelers meet with accidents continues. In the TVK rule, ₹2000 crore per year will b…","metric":"₹20,000 crore","scheme":"","short":"Damage-free Highways","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-273","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Shipping to Sri Lanka, Malaysia from Nagapattinam","desc":"With the aim of reconstructing the ancient Tamils' maritime journeys, TVK government will make necessary arrangements to start maritime journey transport from Nagai port to the cities of Colombo and Kuala Lumpur.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Shipping to Sri","personas":["fisher","all"]},{"id":"t9-274","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Road connecting all Panchayats","desc":"In the next five years, all Panchayats will be connected with highways. All places including schools and primary health centers will be connected by roads in a way that all important places are reachable. Rural Employment Guarantee Scheme will be increased …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Road connecting all","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-275","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Model Villages; Urban Modern Infrastructure for 5000 villages","desc":"As a part of the Tamil Nadu Integrated Development Scheme, 5000 villages will be taken as models first, and ultra-modern infrastructures like in urban areas will be undertaken there. Renewing all water resources, sports grounds, parks, community halls, stre…","metric":"5000 villages","scheme":"","short":"Model Villages; Urban","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-276","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Rural Industrial Infrastructure Scheme","desc":"TVK government will create 1,000 rural industrial clusters (Village Industry Clusters) with integrated infrastructures including professional sheds, electricity, drinking water, roads, logistics (Logistics), storage warehouses, digital connectivity, and bas…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Rural Industrial Infrastructure","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-277","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Rural Markets","desc":"Permanent and weekly markets in every village will be improved with modern infrastructure. Markets will function with weighing machinery, price-showing announcements, refrigerated storage to store green products, direct connection facility with urban wholes…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Rural Markets","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-278","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Climate-Resilient Tamil Nadu Master Plan 2045","desc":"TVK government will create a realistic 'Climate-Resilient Master Plan Draft 2045' that is sustainable and can manage climate change for all districts. Besides identifying and reclaiming to restructure the remaining water bodies and natural ecosystems, sever…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Climate-Resilient Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-279","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Chennai, Trichy, Madurai, Coimbatore Corporations of World-class","desc":"Chennai, Trichy, Madurai, and Coimbatore corporations will be created of world-class with sustainable plans for the future, planned growth in a way that removes residential congestion, modern infrastructure, and improved life.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Chennai, Trichy, Madurai,","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-280","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Various types of Parking","desc":"Various types of modern parking facilities will be brought in corporations as a government and private joint venture. Modern Streets for the people In 25 corporations, streets directly connected with roads will be created as modern streets for the people wi…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Various types of","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-281","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Public Toilet Infrastructure Scheme","desc":"TVK government will build approximately 1.5 lakh public toilets, encompassing a distance of 1 lakh kilometers each on both sides of urban roads. Through this, it will be ensured that toilet facility is available within a distance of 500 meters to 1 kilomete…","metric":"5 lakh","scheme":"","short":"Public Toilet Infrastructure","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t9-282","thoon":9,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Property Tax Reduction","desc":"To reduce the severe property tax hike imposed by the DMK government, the TVK government will introduce a new and fair property tax structure. This will be implemented with the aim of reducing the tax burden of residential owners. Inbam (joy/well-being)","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Property Tax Reduction","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-283","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Victorious Tamil Nadu Super App; Government in your Mobile","desc":"To prevent people from wandering in government offices to receive government service, everyone can receive 500 services including birth certificate, family card, and driving license renewal from their mobile itself through the 'Victorious Tamil Nadu Super A…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Victorious Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-284","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Service without exclusion through Rights Cards","desc":"Like the Aadhaar card, a Rights Card will be provided to every family. Through this, all qualified families can easily receive the benefits for their services. Through this, our government administration will be for everyone in a way that there is no room f…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Service without exclusion","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-285","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamil Nadu Office Monitoring Platform","desc":"TVK government will bring an internet information system called 'Tamil Nadu Office Monitoring Platform' (Real Time Governance Dashboard) into operation. Through this, government income-expenditure accounts, the amount for schemes spent for a constituency an…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Office","personas":["youth","all"]},{"id":"t10-286","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"People's Government; Truth and Honest Administration","desc":"B. Citizens as the Guides of the Government People's Forum; Direct complaints provided by the people will be discussed in the Assembly for a full day A digital platform called 'People's Forum' will be created in a way that people can inform their demands di…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"People's Government; Truth","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-287","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Victorious Tamil Nadu Platform","desc":"Through the 'Victorious Tamil Nadu Platform', all people can undertake telling their ideas to the government, informing acceptance or rejection of government schemes, and evaluating government services from time to time. Right to Choose for the People; 10% …","metric":"10%","scheme":"","short":"Victorious Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-288","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Help Number for People against Bribery","desc":"Bribery continues to rage because people cannot boldly lodge complaints against bribery. Against that, in the TVK rule, the complaint number will be pasted in the central part of all government offices. Recording the behavior of officials who ask for bribes…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Help Number for","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-289","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Strengthening Lokayukta","desc":"Lokayukta will be strengthened by providing the authority to file cases against defaulting officials and elected people's representatives through a transparent appointment method. Inbam (joy/well-being) Thoon 10","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Strengthening Lokayukta","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-290","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamil Nadu Vigilance Monitoring Wing; Bribery will be prevented before it occurs","desc":"Beyond taking action on government irregularities after they have happened, in the TVK rule, the Vigilance Monitoring Wing functioning with technology help will continuously monitor records about procurement and welfare scheme distributions, and money trans…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Vigilance","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-291","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Abolition of Sand Looting","desc":"The method of taking mineral resources and sand will be allowed legally only through transparent auction, in a fair manner.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Abolition of Sand","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-292","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Drug-free Tamil Nadu","desc":"A drug prevention force will be created under the direct monitoring of the Chief Minister. Through this, functioning on a war footing, drug use will be completely removed. Besides those who sell drugs being arrested, they will be confined under the Goondas …","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Drug-free Tamil Nadu","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-293","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Healthy Drug-free Tamil Nadu","desc":"Holding the protection of the welfare of women, families, and homes as the primary objective, the TVK government will follow a steady and gradual approach to reduce alcohol consumption. TVK government will strive to reduce social and financial burdens cause…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Healthy Drug-free Tamil","personas":["woman","all"]},{"id":"t10-294","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Judicial Infrastructure Improvement & Case Pendency Reduction","desc":"New local courts will be established to reduce the number of cases pending in courts and to change justice into something easily accessible to the public. Zero Tolerance for illegal liquor sales TVK government is committed to completely abolishing the produ…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Judicial Infrastructure Improvement","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-295","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Balanced Regional Development Budget","desc":"Tamil Nadu currently has a revenue difference between developed and backward districts at the rate of 3:1. In this budget, schemes for the impartial development of all backward districts including the 12 most backward districts will be formulated.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Balanced Regional Development","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-296","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamil Nadu Cultural and Heritage Budget","desc":"This Tamil Nadu Cultural and Heritage Budget will be tabled for reclaiming and protecting archaeological excavation areas, fund allocation for the currently ongoing Keeladi excavation and next-phase works, and taking Tamil culture to the world stage.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Tamil Nadu Cultural","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-297","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Education and Medicine Equal Opportunity Budget","desc":"This Education and Medicine Equal Opportunity Budget will be tabled for removing the quality difference between educational institutions and hospitals in cities and villages, immediately filling vacant posts of teachers, doctors, and nurses, world-class edu…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Education and Medicine","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-298","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Ecological Budget","desc":"The Ecological Budget will be tabled for protection of maritime resources, making arid districts fertile, flood prevention management in cities, new agricultural methods according to the ecology, and facing climate change.","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Ecological Budget","personas":["fisher","farmer","all"]},{"id":"t10-299","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamil Nadu Strategic Investment Authority (TNSIA)","desc":"TVK government will take Tamil Nadu towards a new economic model that creates wealth, departing from the method of depending only on taxes and subsidies. Whereas previous governments depended only on taxation and concessions, TVK government will establish a…","metric":"","scheme":"Tamil Nadu Strategic Investment Authority (TNSIA)","short":"Tamil Nadu Strategic","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-300","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"White Paper regarding State Financial Position and Debt Management","desc":"TVK government will release an extensive white paper (White Paper) encompassing Tamil Nadu's financial position, debt levels, methods of taking debt, revenue use, and missed economic opportunities. This will serve as a foundation for financial strategies th…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"White Paper regarding","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-301","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Public Sector Undertakings (PSUs) Recovery Scheme","desc":"TVK government will implement structural reforms in all public sector undertakings to improve the operational efficiency of public sector undertakings, increase profit, and reduce the financial burden. Furthermore, besides appointing respective sectoral exp…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Public Sector Undertakings","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-302","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Our request to our valuable voters of Tamil Nadu","desc":"Greetings to every brother and sister on April 23 who is going to decide the fate of our Tamil Nadu and the future of our generations. My dear brothers and sisters, your Vijay's request, Tamil Nadu stands at a turning-point junction of a kind that history w…","metric":"","scheme":"","short":"Our request to","personas":["all"]},{"id":"t10-303","thoon":10,"pillar":"inbam","title":"Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam","desc":"Birth is common to all life!","metric":"","scheme":"Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam","short":"Tamilaga Vettri Kazhagam","personas":["all"]}];
